---

<DefaultLayout title="Blog Component Test">
  <main>
    <div class="bg-white border-b py-8">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Blog Component Test</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          This page demonstrates the Blog React component with category filtering functionality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="container mx-auto py-8 px-4">
      <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Component Demo</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The Blog component below is rendered with the <code>client:visible</code> hydration strategy,
          which means it will be hydrated when it becomes visible in the viewport. 
          This component features:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
          <li>Interactive category filtering</li>
          <li>Responsive grid layout</li>
          <li>Integration with the BlogPostCard component</li>
          <li>Accessible UI controls</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Try clicking on different category filters to see how the blog posts are filtered.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Blog component with client:visible directive as specified in the migration plan -->
      <Blog client:visible posts={samplePosts} title="OUR BLOG" subtitle="LATEST ARTICLES" description="Explore our collection of articles, tutorials, and guides covering various aspects of web development with Astro and modern frontend technologies." />

      <div class="p-6 bg-green-100 rounded-lg shadow-md mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Implementation Notes</h2>
        <p class="mb-2">
          This component has been migrated from the main-theme project to astro-starter according to the React component migration plan.
          Key implementation details:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Uses the <code>client:visible</code> hydration strategy for optimal performance</li>
          <li>Properly integrates with the previously migrated BlogPostCard component</li>
          <li>Implements TypeScript interfaces for type safety</li>
          <li>Includes accessibility features like ARIA attributes and keyboard navigation</li>
          <li>Maintains the original styling and visual design from the main-theme</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</DefaultLayout>